### Exercise 20: Master Challenge

Without using any GUI tools:

1. Monitor logs in real time.
cmd = tail -f /var/log/messages
2. Detect failed SSH logins.
grep -i -e "failed" /var/log/messages | grep ssh
3. Extract usernames involved.
tail -f /var/log/messages | grep -i "failed" | grep -i "ssh" | awk '{for(i=1;i<=NF;i++) if($i=="user" || $i=="for") {print $(i+1); break}}'

4. Save findings into `security_incidents.txt`.
tail -f /var/log/messages | grep -i "failed" | grep -i "password" | awk '{for(i=1;i<=NF;i++) if($i=="user" || $i=="for") {print $(i+1); break}}' >> security_incidents.txt

5. Count total incidents.
wc -l security_incidents.txt
6. Display the five most recent incidents.
tail -n 5 security_incidents.txt
7. Generate a final audit report for management.
echo -e "    REPORT   \nDate: $(date)\nTotal: $(wc -l < security_incidents.txt)\n\nTop Users:\n$(sort security_incidents.txt | uniq -c | sort -nr | head -n 5)\n\nLast 5:\n$(tail -n 5 security_incidents.txt)" > audit_report.txt

